quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  5,114,"Said Jesus the son of Mary, \"O Allah, our Lord! Send down to us a table spread with food from heaven, to be a feast for us, for the first of us and for the last of us, and a sign from Thee. Give us sustenance, for Thou art the best of Providers"
  5,115,"Allah said, \"Verily, I will send it down to you; but whoever disbelieves amongst you after that, verily, I will punish him with a penalty such as I have not inflicted on any one in all the worlds"
  5,116,"And when Allah said, \"O Jesus, son of Mary! Was it you who did say to men, take me and my mother for two gods, beside Allah?\" He said, \"Glory be to Thee! What could have ailed me that I should have uttered what I had no right to? If I had s"
  5,117,"I never told them save that which Thou didst command me (John7:16), ´Worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord,´ and I was a witness of them so long as I was amongst them (see John17:6); but when Thou didst take me away to Thyself Thou wert t"
  5,118,"If Thou punish them, then lo! They are Thy slaves; and if Thou forgive them (lo! They are the slaves also) Lo! Thou alone are the Mighty and the Wise"
  5,119,"Allah said, \"This is the day when their truthfulness shall profit the truthful, for them are Gardens beneath which rivers flow, wherein they dwell in security for ever. Allah is well pleased with them, and they well pleased with Him; that is the grea"
  5,120,"Unto Allah belongs the kingdom of the heavens, and the earth, and all that is therein, and He has Power to do all things"